quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,91,"And they did not appraise Allāh with true appraisal{1} when they said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., they did not appreciate the extent of His ability and wisdom.,footnotes:2:The Jews, or it may refer to the believers, who are taught by the Qur’ān.
  6,92,"And this is a Book which We have sent down, blessed and confirming what was before it, that you may warn the Mother of Cities [i.e., Makkah] and those around it.{1} Those who believe in the Hereafter believe in it, and they are maintaining their prayers.",footnotes:1:i.e., all other peoples.
  6,93,"And who is more unjust than one who invents a lie about Allāh or says, ",footnotes:1:Striking them, as they are unwilling to give up their souls for judgement.
  7,1,"Alif, Lām, Meem, Ṣād.{1}",footnotes:1:See footnote to 2:1.
  7,2,"[This is] a Book revealed to you, [O Muḥammad] - so let there not be in your breast distress therefrom - that you may warn thereby and as a reminder to the believers."
  7,3,"Follow, [O mankind], what has been revealed to you from your Lord and do not follow other than Him any allies. Little do you remember."